        <!-- Page 3: Sophistication & Policy -->
        <div class="page" data-page="3">
            <div class="content-wrapper">
                <div class="section-header">
                    <div class="section-number">Chapter Three</div>
                    <h2>Sophistication & Support</h2>
                </div>
                
                <div class="article-grid">
                    <div class="main-content">
                        <h3>Sectoral Sophistication</h3>

                        <p>The sector has moved substantially upmarket. Whilst customer service remains the foundation‚Äîparticularly for Italian and German clients‚ÄîAlbanian firms have expanded into higher-value services. Financial process outsourcing has grown. Technical support and IT services have become significant offerings. Data analytics and digital transformation, services that would have been unthinkable a decade ago, are now standard fare.</p>

                        <p>Healthcare and financial technology represent established specialisations. Several firms handle sensitive healthcare data processing, requiring not just technical capability but regulatory compliance. Others support fintech operations, managing everything from customer onboarding to transaction monitoring. These are not the standardised scripts of traditional call centres; they require judgement, expertise, and trust.</p>

                        <div class="pull-quote">
                            <div class="pull-quote-text">What Europe discovers in Albania is simple: competence without compromise, and talent that behaves like a partner‚Äînot an extension.</div>
                            <div class="pull-quote-author">Arjodita Mustali, ABSL President</div>
                        </div>

                        <p>The success has been noted. International players have established presences. The scrutiny validates what local firms have long claimed: Albania offers not just acceptable quality at good prices, but genuine competence at competitive rates.</p>

                        <h3>Policy as Enabler</h3>

                        <p>Government support, often more rhetorical than substantive in developing markets, appears genuine in Albania's case. The Albanian Investment Development Agency (AIDA) actively promotes the sector, serving as an intermediary between foreign investors and government bodies. Recent initiatives include funding schemes for technology upgrades and e-commerce platforms, with applications processed within the fiscal year.</p>

                        <p>More ambitious is Durana Tech Park, Albania's first science and technology park, which officially opened in April 2025 with its first cohort of 24 companies, six start-ups, two digital nomads, and two academic institutions. Located in Xhafzotaj, near the Port of Durr√´s, the park offers the usual incentives: zero per cent VAT, zero per cent profit tax for resident companies, and zero per cent personal income tax for employees for ten years.</p>

                        <div class="stats-grid">
                            <div class="stat-box">
                                <span class="stat-value">5,000</span>
                                <div class="stat-description">High-skill jobs projected at Durana Tech Park</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="stat-box">
                                <span class="stat-value">‚Ç¨3.5B</span>
                                <div class="stat-description">Technology exports over 20 years</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="pull-quote">
                            <div class="pull-quote-text">German demand for dependable BPO capacity keeps outpacing supply. In Albania we already see multilingual teams serving German brands with audited processes, GDPR-aligned delivery and same-day collaboration.</div>
                            <div class="pull-quote-author">Annabell Kreuzer, GIZ Western Balkans</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="sidebar">
                        <div class="data-card">
                            <div class="data-number">0%</div>
